revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High use|11,000+}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE. -->
{{shortcut|Template:Notdone}}
This template is often used on [[Wikipedia:talk pages|talk pages]] to show clearly that a section of discussion has not been resolved, so that each editor does not have to completely re-read the section.

==Usage==
You may either use {{tl|not done}} by itself for the default message or you may add a custom message as an optional parameter.

{| class="wikitable"
!Template !! Result
|-
|{{tlx|not done}} || {{not done}}
|-
|{{tlx|not done|Custom message}} || {{not done|Custom message}}
|}

==Example==
{| border="1" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" 
|
{{pseudoheading|Lack of images}}
I think this article needs more pictures. --[[User:Example|John]] 03:25, 12 January 2007<br>
:I agree, especially the part about the estate grounds. --[[User:Example|Jane]] 12:06, 12 January 2007<br>
:Can anyone find any, I've looked on Commons but there doesn't appear to be any. --[[User:Example|George]] 14:31, 13 January 2007<br>
:{{not done}} The only pictures I can find are copyrighted, can anyone else help? --[[User:Example|John]] 20:28, 27 January 2007<br>
:Can anyone take some photos? --[[User:Example|Jane]] 13:51, 3 February 2007<br>
::{{done}} I've uploaded one I took myself. --[[User:Example|John]] 11:38, 7 February 2007<br>
:::{{Thank you}}, that looks great. --[[User:Example|George]] 11:49, 7 February 2007
|}

==TemplateData==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "This template adds a red x mark with text and is often used on talk pages to show clearly that a section of discussion has not been resolved.",
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"label": "custom message",
			"type": "string",
			"default": "Not done",
			"description": "Enter an individual message to replace the default 'Not Done' text."
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

==See also==
{{Done/See also}}

